data: {"type":"response.output_text.done","sequence_number":226,"item_id":"msg_08c56eb3b5582a73006933853ac4bc819788aff55e713a7481","output_index":2,"content_index":0,"text":"Contoso Electronics has a Whistleblower Policy that encourages employees, contractors, and third parties to report any unethical or illegal activities. Here are key points from the policy:\n\n- **Definition:** A whistleblower is an individual who reports activities considered illegal, unethical, or not in accordance with company policy.\n\n- **Reporting Procedures:** Employees can report incidents by contacting the Human Resources Department, emailing the Compliance Officer at compliance@contoso.com, or calling the Compliance Hotline at 1-800-555-1212, with the option for anonymous reporting available.\n\n- **Details Required:** Reports should include the time and date of the incident, involved parties, a description of what happened, and any evidence related to the incident.\n\n- **Retaliation Prohibited:** Retaliation against whistleblowers is strictly forbidden, and disciplinary action will be taken against those who engage in retaliatory behavior.\n\n- **Confidentiality:** The policy ensures that the identity of the whistleblower will be kept confidential as permitted by law.\n\n- **Investigation:** All reports will be investigated promptly and thoroughly.","logprobs":[]}

